        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 6:55PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 650 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms from near
Shelby south to Choteau with stronger embedded storms near Valier
and southwest of Shelby. These storms were moving northeast at 25
mph. In additional to lightning, Strong wind gusts to to 50 mph are
possible with any of these storms with small hail and brief moderate
rainfall beneath stronger cells.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shelby, Conrad, Choteau, Valier, Brady, Dupuyer, Ethridge, Pishkun
Reservoir, Ledger, Collins, Bynum, Pendroy, and Farmington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
